The paper presents a novel deep learning task for uncovering the structure of visual data, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an end-to-end CNN model for this task, which involves training a neural network, making it likely to belong to the categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses Sinkhorn iterations, which are a type of optimization algorithm, making it possible for the paper to belong to the category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper demonstrates the utility of the proposed method on two challenging computer vision problems, which could make it relevant to the category cs.CL (Computation and Language).
